{
    "body": "<p>Kobolds are defined by their class levels&mdash;they do not possess racial Hit Dice. A kobold with NPC class levels takes a &ndash;3 penalty to its CR (rather than the normal &ndash;2 penalty). All kobolds have the following racial traits.</p>", 
    "name": "Kobold", 
    "source": "Bestiary", 
    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Kobold/Kobold", 
    "type": "race", 
    "section_id": 1914, 
    "subtype": "monster_race", 
    "sections": [
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds are fast but weak.</p>", 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "-4 Strength, +2 Dexterity, -2 Constitution", 
            "section_id": 1915
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds are Small and gain a +1 size bonus to their AC, a +1 size bonus on attack rolls, a &ndash;1 penalty to their CMB and CMD, and a +4 size bonus on Stealth checks.</p>", 
            "name": "Small", 
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Kobold/Kobold/Small", 
            "section_id": 1916, 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds have a base speed of 30 feet.</p>", 
            "name": "Normal Speed", 
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Kobold/Kobold/Normal Speed", 
            "section_id": 1917, 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds can see in the dark up to 60 feet.</p>", 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Darkvision", 
            "section_id": 1918
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds have a +1 natural armor bonus.</p>", 
            "name": "Armor", 
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Kobold/Kobold/Armor", 
            "section_id": 1919, 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds gain a +2 racial bonus on Craft (trapmaking), Perception, and Profession (miner) checks. Craft (trapmaking) and Stealth are always class skills for a kobold.</p>", 
            "name": "Crafty", 
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Kobold/Kobold/Crafty", 
            "section_id": 1920, 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Light sensitivity.</p>", 
            "name": "Weakness", 
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary/Monsters/Kobold/Kobold/Weakness", 
            "section_id": 1921, 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Kobolds begin play speaking only Draconic. Kobolds who have high Intelligence scores can choose any of the following bonus languages: Dwarven, Gnome, and Undercommon.</p>", 
            "source": "Bestiary", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Languages", 
